            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ονας ὅστις <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> ἔχει </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Quod neque conatus quisquanst neque <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">adhuc</supplied><supplied reason="lost">adhuc</supplied> <lb n="2"/>noscite rem ut famaa facta feramus virei <lb n="3"/>auspicio <del rend="erasure">An<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>on<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied> Ma<supplied reason="lost">r</supplied>c</del>i proconsule classis <lb n="4"/>Isthmum traductast missaque per pelagus <lb n="5"/>ipse iter eire profectus Sidam classem Hirrus Atheneis <lb n="6"/>pro praetore anni e tempore constituit <lb n="7"/>lucibus haec paucis parvo perfecta tumultu <lb n="8"/>magna <supplied reason="lost">ac qu</supplied>om ratione atque salut<supplied reason="lost">e simul</supplied> <lb n="9"/>q<supplied reason="lost">u</supplied>ei probus est lauda<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied> quei contra est inv<supplied reason="lost">idet illum</supplied> <lb n="10"/>invid<supplied reason="lost">ea</supplied>nt dum q<supplied reason="lost">uos cond</supplied>ecet id v<supplied reason="lost">ideant</supplied>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B): Abweichende Textgestaltung in Z.3. Die griechische Inschrift ist ins 4. Jh. v.Chr. zu datieren. Sie steht auf der oberen Kante des mit der lateinischen Inschrift versehenen Inschriftfeldes.</p>
